<TITLE> Classes start at JU from Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University, Jan 1 (bdnews24.com)  Students should start their classes at Jahangirnagar University from Saturday while seats would not be ready for them at the residential halls. Some 1,500 students had taken admission in 27 departments and two institutes in the campus, Md Farhad Hossain, pro vice chancellor (admin) told bdnews24.com. The university authorities recently said allotment of seats for all new students is not possible, but they will be attached to different halls. Seats would be allotted for them in phases, they said. Five double-decker buses have been arranged to run every week day between Dhaka city and the campus on three routesFazlul Huq Hall- JU campus, Zia Airport-JU campus and Kallyanpur-JU campus. Students would be allotted seats in the newly built Shaheed Rafique-Jabbar Hall within a few months, the pro VC said. The newcomers have been asked to report to their respective departments on the first day and their names would be cut off from the register for a 10-day absence from the start of the classes, the authorities said in a statement. bdnews24.c
